<p>[15] <a href="https://www.scribd.com/document/529594699/Association-Rule-Mining">https://www.scribd.com</a></p>
<p>Lift is a machine learning metric used in association rule mining to measure how much more likely item Y is purchased when item X is purchased, compared to how popular item Y is on its own. [1, 2, 3]</p>
<p>It determines if the relationship between two items is a genuine pattern or just a random coincidence. [4, 5]</p>
<hr>
<h2 id="the-formula">The Formula</h2>
<p>The formula for Lift calculates the ratio of the Support of both items together to the individual Support of each item multiplied:</p>
<p><span class="katex--display"><span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mtext>Lift</mtext><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mtext>Support</mtext><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>∪</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mtext>Support</mtext><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>×</mo><mtext>Support</mtext><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mfrac></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\text{Lift}(X \rightarrow Y) = \frac{\text{Support}(X \cup Y)}{\text{Support}(X) \times \text{Support}(Y)}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Lift</span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.07847em;">X</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.277778em;"></span><span class="mrel">→</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.277778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.22222em;">Y</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.277778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.277778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 2.363em; vertical-align: -0.936em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mopen nulldelimiter"></span><span class="mfrac"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 1.427em;"><span class="" style="top: -2.314em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Support</span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.07847em;">X</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.222222em;"></span><span class="mbin">×</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.222222em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Support</span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.22222em;">Y</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.23em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="frac-line" style="border-bottom-width: 0.04em;"></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.677em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Support</span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.07847em;">X</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.222222em;"></span><span class="mbin">∪</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.222222em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.22222em;">Y</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.936em;"><span class=""></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose nulldelimiter"></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p>Alternatively, it can be written using Confidence:</p>
<p><span class="katex--display"><span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mtext>Lift</mtext><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mtext>Confidence</mtext><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mtext>Support</mtext><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mfrac></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\text{Lift}(X \rightarrow Y) = \frac{\text{Confidence}(X \rightarrow Y)}{\text{Support}(Y)}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Lift</span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.07847em;">X</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.277778em;"></span><span class="mrel">→</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.277778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.22222em;">Y</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.277778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.277778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 2.363em; vertical-align: -0.936em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mopen nulldelimiter"></span><span class="mfrac"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 1.427em;"><span class="" style="top: -2.314em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Support</span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.22222em;">Y</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.23em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="frac-line" style="border-bottom-width: 0.04em;"></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.677em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Confidence</span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.07847em;">X</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.277778em;"></span><span class="mrel">→</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.277778em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.22222em;">Y</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.936em;"><span class=""></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose nulldelimiter"></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<ul>
<li><span class="katex--inline"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext>Support</mtext><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>∪</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\text{Support}(X \cup Y)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Support</span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.07847em;">X</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.222222em;"></span><span class="mbin">∪</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.222222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.22222em;">Y</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span></span>: The percentage of total transactions containing both X and Y.</li>
<li><span class="katex--inline"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext>Support</mtext><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\text{Support}(X)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Support</span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.07847em;">X</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span></span>: The percentage of total transactions containing X.</li>
<li><span class="katex--inline"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext>Support</mtext><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\text{Support}(Y)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Support</span></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.22222em;">Y</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span></span>: The percentage of total transactions containing Y.</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id="how-to-interpret-the-lift-value">How to Interpret the Lift Value</h2>
<ul>
<li>Lift &gt; 1 (Positive Correlation): Highly significant. It means item X and item Y are heavily dependent on each other. Buying X strongly increases the chances of buying Y. [6]</li>
<li>Lift = 1 (No Correlation): The items are completely independent. Buying X has zero effect on whether the customer buys Y. They just happen to appear together by pure random chance. [7, 8]</li>
<li>Lift &lt; 1 (Negative Correlation): The items look for alternatives. Buying X means the customer is less likely to buy Y (e.g., choosing Coke makes them unlikely to buy Pepsi in the same trip). [9]</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id="quick-calculation-example">Quick Calculation Example</h2>
<p>Imagine a supermarket with 100 total transactions:</p>
<ul>
<li>40 transactions contain Milk [Support(Milk) = 0.40]</li>
<li>30 transactions contain Cereal [Support(Cereal) = 0.30]</li>
<li>20 transactions contain both Milk and Cereal [Support(Both) = 0.20]</li>
</ul>
<p>Lift for the rule: <span class="katex--inline"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext>Milk</mtext><mo>→</mo><mtext>Cereal</mtext></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\text{Milk} \rightarrow \text{Cereal}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.69444em; vertical-align: 0em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Milk</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.277778em;"></span><span class="mrel">→</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.277778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.69444em; vertical-align: 0em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Cereal</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p><span class="katex--display"><span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mtext>Lift</mtext><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>0.20</mn><mrow><mn>0.40</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>0.30</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>0.20</mn><mn>0.12</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn mathvariant="bold">1.67</mn></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\text{Lift} = \frac{0.20}{0.40 \times 0.30} = \frac{0.20}{0.12} = \mathbf{1.67}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.69444em; vertical-align: 0em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Lift</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.277778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.277778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 2.09077em; vertical-align: -0.76933em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mopen nulldelimiter"></span><span class="mfrac"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 1.32144em;"><span class="" style="top: -2.314em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">0.40</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.222222em;"></span><span class="mbin">×</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.222222em;"></span><span class="mord">0.30</span></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.23em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="frac-line" style="border-bottom-width: 0.04em;"></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.677em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">0.20</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.76933em;"><span class=""></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose nulldelimiter"></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.277778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.277778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 2.00744em; vertical-align: -0.686em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mopen nulldelimiter"></span><span class="mfrac"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 1.32144em;"><span class="" style="top: -2.314em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">0.12</span></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.23em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="frac-line" style="border-bottom-width: 0.04em;"></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.677em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">0.20</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.686em;"><span class=""></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose nulldelimiter"></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.277778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.277778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.64444em; vertical-align: 0em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathbf">1.67</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p>Interpretation: Because the Lift is 1.67 (which is greater than 1), customers who buy Milk are 1.67 times more likely to buy Cereal compared to an ordinary shopper. This is a great product pairing for a marketing campaign. [10]</p>
