<h2 id="advantages-and-disadvantages">Advantages and Disadvantages</h2>
<h2 id="advantages">Advantages</h2>
<ul>
<li>Simple and Intuitive: Uses an easily understandable logic framework.</li>
<li>Drastic Search Space Reduction: The pruning criteria completely eliminates calculating combinations that are guaranteed to fail. [2, 3, 52, 53, 54]</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="limitations">Limitations</h2>
<ul>
<li>High I/O Overhead: Scanning the entire database at every single itemset length expansion (k) creates a massive performance bottleneck on large enterprise storage engines. [14, 55]</li>
<li>Combinatorial Explosion: If millions of single items are frequent, the candidate generation step (C₂) will balloon exponentially and deplete available system memory. [55]</li>
</ul>
